Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a Multi-Object Tracking (MOT) approach that integrates single object tracking and data association methods using visual features. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed approach uses a cost-sensitive tracking loss and attention mechanisms, which are common techniques in AI-based object tracking. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper introduces a cost-sensitive tracking loss and proposes Dual Matching Attention Networks (DMAN) with attention mechanisms, which are machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics): The proposed approach can be applied to robotics applications such as autonomous vehicles and drones for tracking multiple objects in real-time. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper evaluates the proposed approach on the MOT benchmark datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia research for evaluating object tracking algorithms.
